# Repository agent contract — novelty-theory-lean

1. **First on sustained work:** read repo-root **`QUEUE.md`** (execution contract + cross-epic backlog), then **`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`**, **`docs/000_INDEX.md`**, **`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`**, and the active epic under **`specs/INCOMPLETE/IN-PROCESS/`**.
2. **Specs** (`specs/`) vs **finished docs** (`docs/`): never put normative specs under `docs/`.
3. Cite specs as **`SPEC_NNN_XXX`** (three-digit number + three-character alphanumeric suffix); assign the next free number and a new suffix for every new spec.
4. **Execution discipline:** Keep consuming queue items **yourself**; update **`QUEUE.md`**, epic queues, and checklists **in-repo** as you go. Seek the **strongest** results the spec allows. **STOP AND ASK** only when **genuinely stuck** after exhausting context and tools ([`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`](../../NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md) §5.2). Run until **all epics in scope are complete**, then report to the owner.
5. **Lean:** follow **Proof quality (Lean)** in [`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](../../CODING_PROTOCOLS.md) — minimal `sorry`/axioms, strongest general statements, honest disclosure; **audit** every Lean pass for proof gaps, axioms, vacuous claims, weak lemmas, and definition smuggling (see **[`QUEUE.md`](../../QUEUE.md)** — *Agent execution contract*).
6. **Python / Node:** follow **Code quality (Python, Node, and imperative stacks)** in [`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](../../CODING_PROTOCOLS.md) — tests, types/lint as adopted, root-cause fixes, no error masking.
7. After coherent work: update spec/epic acceptance, **`docs/000_INDEX.md`**, and TODO/debt registries — not only in chat.
8. **Migrations:** never edit already-run migrations; add a new migration file.
9. **Stubs/mocks** require an explicit **TODO** with completion notes.
10. **Git:** when sharing a branch with other agents, prefer commits that touch **only your files**.
11. **External-facing code:** **Role-based** identifiers; comments for **external** readers only — **no self-talk / meta-talk**; **never** name **advisor, user, owner, PI, or any person** in code or comments ([`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](../../CODING_PROTOCOLS.md)).
12. **Lean repo layout:** This repository **is** the **`novelty-theory-lean`** root; **parent** prose repos embed it as **`git submodule`** ([`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`](../../NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md) §7.3).
13. **LaTeX papers:** **References** + `.bib` when applicable; **appendices** (inventory + dependency map) for formal papers; **never** cite internal `docs`/`specs` in paper body (**exception:** public doc URL); **preamble** aligned with **`/Users/nova/representational-incompleteness/lean/paper/Representational_Incompleteness.tex`** ([`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`](../../NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md) §8).

Stack-specific commands belong in **`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`** (Project specifics) and **`docs/002_DEVELOPER_SETUP.md`** (repo root / `docs/`).
